welcome_message_body: "Welcome to Longwood, a charming city known for its vibrant culture and picturesque landscapes. Get ready to explore and immerse yourself in all that Longwood has to offer. We hope you enjoy your stay here!"

terminals.name: Terminal A
terminals.description: The main terminal at Orlando Sanford International Airport, serving domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Terminal B
terminals.description: A secondary terminal at Orlando Sanford International Airport, mainly used for charter and seasonal flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport, no password required.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Orlando Executive Airport serves all commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Orlando Executive Airport caters to private jet and charter flights.

wifi.note: Complimentary WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Kissimmee Gateway Airport handles all commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Cargo Terminal
terminals.description: The cargo terminal at Kissimmee Gateway Airport is used for shipping and receiving goods.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport for free.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Orlando International Airport houses the check-in counters, baggage claim, and security checkpoints.

terminals.name: Terminal A
terminals.description: Terminal A primarily serves domestic flights and is home to many major airlines.

terminals.name: Terminal B
terminals.description: Terminal B serves both domestic and international flights and offers a variety of dining and shopping options.

terminals.name: Terminal C
terminals.description: Terminal C is primarily used by low-cost carriers and offers a more budget-friendly travel experience.

wifi.note: Wi-Fi is available throughout the airport for free with limited access. Premium access is available for purchase.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: This is the main terminal at Leesburg Airport, where most commercial flights operate from.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: This terminal is reserved for private and chartered flights at Leesburg Airport.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport for passengers to use.
